The paper deals with the characterization of the generalized degrees of freedom (GDoF) region of a multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) interference channel with delayed channel state information at transmitters (CSIT). This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also involves the use of digital multicasting and interference quantization, which are techniques commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of the weighted sum-rate, which is a problem commonly studied in control engineering (cs.CE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.CE.
